Data Collection for a Face Mask Detection project split into two types:

Data Collection

Data collection is the process of gathering images required to train the face mask detection model.

1. Manual Labeling
Explanation

Images are collected manually and assigned labels by a human.

Labels
Mask
No Mask
Example
Image 1 → Mask
Image 2 → No Mask
Image 3 → Mask
Advantages
High accuracy
Correct labeling
Better model performance
Disadvantages
Time-consuming
Requires human effort
Use in Face Mask Detection

Create two folders:

dataset/
│
├── with_mask
└── without_mask

and manually place images in the correct folder.

2. Random Data Collection
Explanation

Images are collected automatically from various sources.

Sources
Google Images
Kaggle Datasets
Open Images Dataset
CCTV Images
Internet Sources
Example
1000 Mask Images
1000 No-Mask Images

collected automatically.

Advantages
Fast collection
Large dataset
Less manual effort
Disadvantages
May contain wrong labels
Duplicate images
Noisy data
Use in Face Mask Detection

Download mask and no-mask images from online datasets and then clean them before training.

Face Mask Detection Data Collection Flow
Data Collection
      │
      ├── Manual Labeling
      │      ├── Mask
      │      └── No Mask
      │
      └── Random Data Collection
             ├── Internet Images
             ├── Kaggle Dataset
             └── Google Images
5-Point Exam Answer
Data collection is the first step in face mask detection.
Images can be collected through manual labeling or random data collection.
Manual labeling assigns correct labels such as Mask and No Mask.
Random data collection gathers images from datasets and online sources.
The collected images are used to train the deep learning model for mask classification.


=========

In a Face Mask Detection Project, the dataset folder is the data collection folder.

Dataset Folder Structure
dataset/
│
├── with_mask/
│      ├── image1.jpg
│      ├── image2.jpg
│      ├── image3.jpg
│
└── without_mask/
       ├── image1.jpg
       ├── image2.jpg
       ├── image3.jpg
Explanation
with_mask Folder
Contains images of people wearing face masks.
Label = Mask
without_mask Folder
Contains images of people not wearing face masks.
Label = No Mask
Purpose
Acts as the data collection repository.
Provides training data for the model.
Used by train_mask_detector.py during training.
Workflow
Data Collection
       ↓
dataset/
       ↓
train_mask_detector.py
       ↓
mask_detector.model
       ↓
Prediction (Mask / No Mask)
Short Exam Answer

The dataset folder is the data collection folder in a Face Mask Detection project. It contains images categorized into with_mask and without_mask folders, which are used to train the deep learning model.
